<p><b>GARDENYX</b></p>
<p><b>Privacy Policy</b></p>
<p><i>Mobile Application</i></p>
<p>Effective Date: March 6, 2026</p>
<p><b>1. Introduction</b></p>
<p>This Privacy Policy describes how JOINA Garden, s. r. o., with its registered office at Karpatské námestie 7770/10A, Bratislava – mestská časť Rača 831 06, Slovak Republic, IČO: 57 313 504 ("we", "us", "our", "Company"), collects, uses, stores, and protects your personal data when you use the GardenYX mobile application ("App") available on iOS, Android, and as a progressive web application.</p>
<p>We are committed to protecting your privacy in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 ("GDPR") and applicable Slovak data protection legislation. By using the App, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p><b>2. Data Controller</b></p>
<p><b>Company: </b>JOINA Garden, s. r. o.</p>
<p><b>Address: </b>Karpatské námestie 7770/10A, Bratislava – mestská časť Rača 831 06, Slovak Republic</p>
<p><b>IČO: </b>57 313 504</p>
<p><b>Email: </b>privacy@gardenyx.eu</p>
<p><b>3. Personal Data We Collect</b></p>
<p><b>3.1 Account Information</b></p>
<p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Email address (required for authentication and account verification)</li>
  <li>Display name or username (required for your user profile)</li>
  <li>Profile photo URL (optional, for profile display)</li>
  <li>A unique user identifier generated by Firebase Authentication</li>
  <li>Account creation and update timestamps</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.2 Authentication Data</b></p>
<p>You may sign in using one of the following methods. Each method involves data processed by the respective provider:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Email and password (via Firebase Authentication)</li>
  <li>Google Sign-In (via Google OAuth)</li>
  <li>Sign in with Apple (via Apple OAuth)</li>
  <li>Anonymous sign-in (temporary account for trial use, deleted upon registration)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.3 Plant-Related Data</b></p>
<p>When you use the App to manage your plants, we collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Plant names (common and scientific), taxonomy, plant type</li>
  <li>Plant images you capture or upload</li>
  <li>Plant location or room information</li>
  <li>Plant notes, age, and care history (watering dates, care schedules)</li>
  <li>Care preferences (light requirements, pot drainage, repotting history)</li>
  <li>Notification preferences for individual plants</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.4 Usage and Analytics Data</b></p>
<p>We automatically collect certain data about how you use the App:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Screen and page views (via Firebase Analytics)</li>
  <li>Plant health diagnosis history and results</li>
  <li>Plant identification attempts and results</li>
  <li>Care task completion logs</li>
  <li>Conversations with the AI assistant (chat history)</li>
  <li>Calendar event data (watering, fertilizing, repotting tasks)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.5 Device Information</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Device model and operating system version</li>
  <li>App version and build number</li>
  <li>Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) token for push notifications</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.6 Camera and Media Data</b></p>
<p>With your permission, we access:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Plant photos captured via your device camera</li>
  <li>Images selected from your photo library</li>
  <li>Photo metadata (dimensions, file size)</li>
  <li>Health diagnosis images</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.7 Subscription Data</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Subscription status and active entitlements</li>
  <li>Active subscription dates</li>
</ul>
<p>Payment information is handled exclusively by RevenueCat, the Apple App Store, or Google Play. We do not store your payment card details.</p>
<p><b>4. How We Use Your Data</b></p>
<p>We process your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Account management: </b>to create, maintain, and secure your account</li>
  <li><b>Plant care services: </b>to provide plant tracking, care reminders, AI-powered plant identification, health diagnosis, and personalized care recommendations</li>
  <li><b>AI features: </b>to power the AI chatbot (RastoAI), plant identification (Plant.id API), plant information enrichment (GPT integration), and health diagnosis</li>
  <li><b>Notifications: </b>to send push notifications for watering, fertilizing, and repotting reminders</li>
  <li><b>Analytics and improvement: </b>to understand how the App is used and to improve our services (Firebase Analytics)</li>
  <li><b>Crash reporting: </b>to identify and fix technical issues (Firebase Crashlytics)</li>
  <li><b>Subscription management: </b>to manage your subscription status and premium features (RevenueCat)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>4.1 Legal Basis for Processing</b></p>
<p>We process your data based on the following legal grounds under the GDPR:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Contract performance (Art. 6(1)(b)): </b>processing necessary to provide you with the App services you requested</li>
  <li><b>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a)): </b>for optional features such as camera access, photo library access, and push notifications. You may withdraw consent at any time through your device settings.</li>
  <li><b>Legitimate interests (Art. 6(1)(f)): </b>for analytics, crash reporting, and service improvement, where our interests do not override your fundamental rights</li>
</ul>
<p><b>5. Third-Party Services and Data Sharing</b></p>
<p>We share data with the following third-party service providers who process data on our behalf or as independent controllers:</p>
<p><b>5.1 Firebase (Google LLC)</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Firebase Authentication – user sign-up, login, session management</li>
  <li>Cloud Firestore – user profile data storage</li>
  <li>Firebase Storage – plant photo and diagnosis image storage</li>
  <li>Firebase Cloud Messaging – push notifications</li>
  <li>Firebase Analytics – usage analytics and event tracking</li>
  <li>Firebase Crashlytics – crash reporting and error logging</li>
</ul>
<p>Google’s privacy policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy</p>
<p><b>5.2 Payment and Subscription Providers</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>RevenueCat – subscription management and entitlement tracking</li>
  <li>Apple App Store – iOS payment processing</li>
  <li>Google Play Billing – Android payment processing</li>
</ul>
<p><b>5.3 Plant Identification and Data Services</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Plant.id API – plant image identification (receives plant images)</li>
  <li>Perenual API – plant database and information lookup (receives plant names)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>5.4 AI Services</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>RastoAI (custom backend) – AI plant care chatbot (receives user chat messages)</li>
  <li>GPT integration (via backend) – plant information enrichment (receives plant scientific names and language preference)</li>
  <li>Diagnosis API (backend) – plant health diagnosis (receives health diagnosis images)</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not sell your personal data to any third party.</p>
<p><b>6. International Data Transfers</b></p>
<p>Some of our third-party service providers (notably Firebase/Google and RevenueCat) operate globally. Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries outside the European Economic Area (EEA). Where such transfers occur, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place, including Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission or the service provider’s participation in recognized certification mechanisms.</p>
<p><b>7. Data Storage and Security</b></p>
<p><b>7.1 Local Storage</b></p>
<p>The App stores certain data locally on your device:</p>
<ul>
  <li>SQLite database for plant data, care schedules, and watering history</li>
  <li>Shared preferences for user settings (theme, language, text scale)</li>
  <li>Encrypted sensitive data via Flutter Secure Storage</li>
  <li>Session cookies for backend session management</li>
</ul>
<p><b>7.2 Cloud Storage</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Cloud Firestore – user profiles</li>
  <li>Firebase Storage – plant photos and diagnosis images</li>
  <li>Dakoty backend server – plants, gardens, care schedules, reminders, user accounts, chat history, diagnosis history, notifications, and FCM tokens</li>
</ul>
<p><b>7.3 Security Measures</b></p>
<p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data, including password encryption, encrypted storage for sensitive data, and HTTPS for all network communication.</p>
<p><b>8. Data Retention</b></p>
<p>We retain your personal data for as long as your account remains active. If you delete your account, we will delete or anonymize your data within 30 days, unless we are legally required to retain certain data for a longer period.</p>
<p>Anonymous accounts created for trial use are automatically deleted when you register a full account.</p>
<p><b>9. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</b></p>
<p>The App uses session cookies stored locally on your device for backend session management. These cookies persist across app restarts and are used solely for maintaining your authenticated session.</p>
<p>Firebase Analytics is enabled by default and tracks screen views and custom events. Firebase Crashlytics is used for crash reporting. Both are operated by Google and are subject to Google’s privacy policy.</p>
<p><b>10. Your Rights Under the GDPR</b></p>
<p>As a data subject, you have the following rights:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Right of access (Art. 15): </b>obtain confirmation of whether your data is being processed and receive a copy</li>
  <li><b>Right to rectification (Art. 16): </b>have inaccurate data corrected</li>
  <li><b>Right to erasure (Art. 17): </b>request deletion of your personal data</li>
  <li><b>Right to restriction (Art. 18): </b>restrict the processing of your data in certain circumstances</li>
  <li><b>Right to data portability (Art. 20): </b>receive your data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format</li>
  <li><b>Right to object (Art. 21): </b>object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
  <li><b>Right to withdraw consent: </b>where processing is based on consent, you may withdraw it at any time without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at privacy@gardenyx.eu. We will respond within 30 days. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Office for Personal Data Protection of the Slovak Republic (Úrad na ochranu osobných údajov SR).</p>
<p><b>11. Account Deletion</b></p>
<p>You can delete your account at any time via the Settings section in the App. Upon deletion, the following data is removed:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Your Firebase user account</li>
  <li>Your backend user profile</li>
  <li>All local plant database entries</li>
  <li>All cached provider states</li>
  <li>Your FCM token</li>
</ul>
<p>Please note that some data may persist in backups for a limited period and will be deleted in accordance with our backup retention schedule.</p>
<p><b>12. Children’s Privacy</b></p>
<p>The App is not directed at children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 16. If you become aware that a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us at privacy@gardenyx.eu and we will take steps to delete such data.</p>
<p><b>13. Device Permissions</b></p>
<p>The App may request the following permissions on your device:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Camera: </b>to take plant photos for identification and health diagnosis</li>
  <li><b>Photo library (read): </b>to select existing plant images</li>
  <li><b>Photo library (write): </b>to save images to your device</li>
  <li><b>Notifications: </b>to send care reminders for watering, fertilizing, and repotting</li>
</ul>
<p>All permissions are optional and can be managed through your device settings at any time.</p>
<p><b>14. Automated Decision-Making and AI</b></p>
<p>The App uses artificial intelligence for plant identification, health diagnosis, and care recommendations. These features process plant images and data to provide automated suggestions. The AI features are advisory in nature and do not produce legal or similarly significant effects on you. You are free to disregard any AI-generated recommendation.</p>
<p><b>15. Changes to This Privacy Policy</b></p>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by posting the updated policy in the App or by other appropriate means. The "Effective Date" at the top of this document indicates when the latest version became effective.</p>
